Detectives on Friday night shot and killed a man suspected of shooting dead a police officer. Police say they received a tip-off and trailed the said suspect to Githurai Kimbo. According to the police, the suspect defied orders to surrender before he was fatally shot. A pistol with nine rounds ammunition was recovered from the suspect. The slain suspect is reported to have shot and killed a police officer before fleeing with his official firearm.   Families of 23 men executed by police want government to form a commission of inquiry.